{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775868360899,"sessionID":"ses_285ff8cd3ffeYfvxMfbpOKDTUs","part":{"id":"prt_d7a00a3c4001CpPnlMrNsxTuSB","messageID":"msg_d7a0094e200109mSGQ3ObVpCg2","sessionID":"ses_285ff8cd3ffeYfvxMfbpOKDTUs","type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"toolu_88b3c4c4ea34425da1462349","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-qwen3.5-plus_20260410T163217Z/changes/AR-022/proposal.md"},"output":"<path>/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-qwen3.5-plus_20260410T163217Z/changes/AR-022/proposal.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: # AR-022: CLI Publish Command\n2: \n3: ## Purpose\n4: \n5: This proposal implements the `publish` command for the AgentCube Python CLI toolkit. The `publish` command deploys agents to Kubernetes or AgentCube platform using either the standard Kubernetes provider (Deployment + NodePort Service) or the AgentCube provider (AgentRuntime CR). This command completes the agent deployment workflow after `pack` and `build` commands.\n6: \n7: The goal is to:\n8: \n9: 1. **Support dual-provider deployment** - Enable deployment to standard Kubernetes (Deployment/Service) or AgentCube platform (AgentRuntime CR) via `--provider` flag\n10: 2. **Handle image preparation** - Prepare container images via local Docker push or accept pre-built image URLs for cloud build mode\n11: 3. **Manage deployment lifecycle** - Create or patch Kubernetes resources, wait for rollout readiness, and report deployment status\n12: 4. **Persist deployment metadata** - Update agent metadata with deployment information including agent_id, endpoint URLs, and session configuration\n13: \n14: This implementation builds upon the CLI toolkit specification (`cli-toolkit/spec.md`, `cli-toolkit/design.md`) and leverages the Kubernetes provider patterns from `deployment/client-go.md`.\n15: \n16: ## Scope\n17: \n18: **Module:** `cmd/cli`  \n19: **Language:** Python  \n20: **Size:** L\n21: \n22: This AR covers:\n23: \n24: - **In scope:**\n25:   - `PublishRuntime` class implementation with all specified methods\n26:   - `publish` Typer command with all specified options (workspace, version, image_url, credentials, provider, node_port, replicas, namespace, etc.)\n27:   - AgentCube provider integration for AgentRuntime CR deployment\n28:   - Standard Kubernetes provider integration for Deployment/Service\n29:   - Image preparation logic for local and cloud build modes\n30:   - Readiness probe waiting with 120s timeout\n31:   - Metadata updates for deployment information\n32:   - Error handling with verbose traceback support\n33:   - Unit tests for publish logic\n34:   - Documentation and usage examples\n35: \n36: - **Out of scope:**\n37:   - `build` command implementation (assumes pre-built image or local Docker availability)\n38:   - Advanced rollout strategies (canary, blue-green)\n39:   - Multi-cluster deployment\n40:   - Custom resource definition management (assumes CRDs already installed)\n41: \n42: ## Current State Analysis\n43: \n44: ### AR-020 Pack Command\n45: \n46: AR-020 established:\n47: - `agentcube` Python package structure under `cmd/cli/`\n48: - `PackRuntime` class with workspace validation and Dockerfile generation\n49: - `AgentMetadata` Pydantic model with 22 fields\n50: - `MetadataService` for loading/saving `agent_metadata.yaml`\n51: - CLI entry point with Typer framework\n52: \n53: ### CLI Toolkit Specification\n54: \n55: Per `cli-toolkit/spec.md` and `cli-toolkit/design.md`:\n56: - `publish` command options: workspace, version, image_url, image_username, image_password, description, region, cloud_provider, provider, node_port, replicas, namespace, verbose\n57: - Provider options: `agentcube` (AgentRuntime CR) or `k8s` (Deployment/Service)\n58: - `PublishRuntime` class with 8 methods specified\n59: - AgentCube provider prerequisites: requires `router_url` and `workload_manager_url` in metadata\n60: - Standard K8s publish flow: deploy_agent → wait_for_deployment_ready → update metadata\n61: \n62: ### Kubernetes Client-Go Patterns\n63: \n64: Per `deployment/client-go.md`:\n65: - CRD API group: `runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh/v1alpha1`\n66: - CRD plural: `agentruntimes`\n67: - Typed client interface: `AgentRuntimeInterface` with Create/Update/Get/Delete methods\n68: - CustomObjectsApi for dynamic CR operations\n69: \n70: ### Gaps Identified\n71: \n72: 1. **No PublishRuntime implementation** - Only stub exists from AR-020\n73: 2. **No provider integration** - KubernetesProvider and AgentCubeProvider are stubs\n74: 3. **No image preparation logic** - No Docker push or image URL handling\n75: 4. **No readiness waiting** - No deployment readiness polling\n76: 5. **No AgentRuntime CR schema** - CR structure not fully specified\n77: \n78: ## Proposed Changes\n79: \n80: ### 1. PublishRuntime Implementation\n81: \n82: ```python\n83: # agentcube/runtime/publish_runtime.py\n84: \"\"\"PublishRuntime for deploying agents.\"\"\"\n85: \n86: from __future__ import annotations\n87: \n88: import logging\n89: from pathlib import Path\n90: from typing import Any, Dict, Optional\n91: \n92: from agentcube.services.metadata_service import AgentMetadata, MetadataService\n93: from agentcube.services.docker_service import DockerService\n94: from agentcube.services.k8s_provider import KubernetesProvider\n95: from agentcube.services.agentcube_provider import AgentCubeProvider\n96: \n97: logger = logging.getLogger(__name__)\n98: \n99: \n100: class PublishRuntime:\n101:     \"\"\"Runtime for publishing agents to Kubernetes or AgentCube.\"\"\"\n102: \n103:     def __init__(self, verbose: bool = False, provider: str = \"agentcube\") -> None:\n104:         self.verbose = verbose\n105:         self.provider = provider\n106:         self.metadata_service = MetadataService(verbose=verbose)\n107:         self.docker_service = DockerService(verbose=verbose)\n108:         if verbose:\n109:             logging.basicConfig(level=logging.DEBUG)\n110: \n111:     def publish(self, workspace_path: Path, **options: Any) -> Dict[str, Any]:\n112:         \"\"\"Publish an agent to Kubernetes or AgentCube.\"\"\"\n113:         logger.debug(f\"Publishing agent from workspace: {workspace_path}\")\n114: \n115:         # Load metadata\n116:         metadata = self.metadata_service.load_metadata(workspace_path)\n117: \n118:         # Apply CLI overrides\n119:         self._apply_publish_options(metadata, options)\n120: \n121:         # Validate prerequisites\n122:         self._validate_publish_prerequisites(metadata, options)\n123: \n124:         # Prepare image for publishing\n125:         image_url = self._prepare_image_for_publishing(workspace_path, metadata, options)\n126: \n127:         # Deploy based on provider\n128:         if self.provider == \"agentcube\":\n129:             agent_info = self._publish_cr_to_k8s(workspace_path, metadata, image_url, **options)\n130:         elif self.provider == \"k8s\":\n131:             agent_info = self._publish_k8s(workspace_path, metadata, image_url, **options)\n132:         else:\n133:             raise ValueError(f\"Unsupported provider: {self.provider}\")\n134: \n135:         # Update publish metadata\n136:         self._update_publish_metadata(workspace_path, agent_info)\n137: \n138:         logger.info(f\"Successfully published agent: {metadata.agent_name}\")\n139: \n140:         return agent_info\n141: \n142:     def _apply_publish_options(self, metadata: AgentMetadata, options: Dict[str, Any]) -> None:\n143:         \"\"\"Apply CLI option overrides to metadata.\"\"\"\n144:         updates: Dict[str, Any] = {}\n145: \n146:         for field in [\n147:             \"version\", \"description\", \"region\", \"registry_url\",\n148:             \"registry_username\", \"registry_password\", \"agent_endpoint\",\n149:         ]:\n150:             value = options.get(field)\n151:             if value is not None and value != \"\":\n152:                 updates[field] = value\n153: \n154:         # Handle namespace separately (not in AgentMetadata initially)\n155:         namespace = options.get(\"namespace\")\n156:         if namespace:\n157:             updates[\"namespace\"] = namespace\n158: \n159:         if updates:\n160:             logger.debug(f\"Applying publish overrides: {updates}\")\n161:             metadata_dict = metadata.model_dump()\n162:             metadata_dict.update(updates)\n163:             # Note: May need to extend AgentMetadata with namespace field\n164: \n165:     def _validate_publish_prerequisites(self, metadata: AgentMetadata, options: Dict[str, Any]) -> None:\n166:         \"\"\"Validate prerequisites for publishing.\"\"\"\n167:         # Check build mode\n168:         if metadata.build_mode == \"local\":\n169:             # Local mode requires Docker\n170:             if not self.docker_service.check_docker_available():\n171:                 raise RuntimeError(\"Docker is not available or not running\")\n172: \n173:         # AgentCube provider prerequisites\n174:         if self.provider == \"agentcube\":\n175:             if not metadata.router_url or not metadata.workload_manager_url:\n176:                 raise ValueError(\n177:                     \"AgentCube provider requires 'router_url' and 'workload_manager_url' \"\n178:                     \"in agent_metadata.yaml. Please run 'pack' with --router-url and \"\n179:                     \"--workload-manager-url options.\"\n180:                 )\n181: \n182:         # Validate image URL for cloud mode\n183:         if metadata.build_mode == \"cloud\" and not options.get(\"image_url\"):\n184:             raise ValueError(\n185:                 \"Cloud build mode requires --image-url to be specified\"\n186:             )\n187: \n188:     def _publish_cr_to_k8s(self, workspace_path: Path, metadata: AgentMetadata, image_url: str, **options: Any) -> Dict[str, Any]:\n189:         \"\"\"Publish using AgentCube AgentRuntime CR.\"\"\"\n190:         logger.info(\"Deploying AgentRuntime CR to Kubernetes\")\n191: \n192:         provider = AgentCubeProvider(\n193:             namespace=options.get(\"namespace\", \"default\"),\n194:             verbose=self.verbose,\n195:         )\n196: \n197:         # Prepare readiness probe\n198:         readiness_probe_path = metadata.readiness_probe_path or \"/health\"\n199:         readiness_probe_port = metadata.readiness_probe_port or metadata.port\n200: \n201:         # Deploy AgentRuntime CR\n202:         result = provider.deploy_agent_runtime(\n203:             agent_name=metadata.agent_name,\n204:             image_url=image_url,\n205:             port=metadata.port,\n206:             entrypoint=metadata.entrypoint,\n207:             env_vars=self._build_agent_env_vars(metadata),\n208:             workload_manager_url=metadata.workload_manager_url,\n209:             router_url=metadata.router_url,\n210:             readiness_probe_path=readiness_probe_path,\n211:             readiness_probe_port=readiness_probe_port,\n212:         )\n213: \n214:         # Wait for deployment readiness\n215:         provider.wait_for_deployment_ready(metadata.agent_name, timeout=120)\n216: \n217:         # Get final status\n218:         status = provider.get_agent_runtime(metadata.agent_name)\n219: \n220:         return {\n221:             \"agent_name\": metadata.agent_name,\n222:             \"agent_id\": metadata.agent_name,  # CR name as ID\n223:             \"deployment_type\": \"AgentRuntime\",\n224:             \"namespace\": options.get(\"namespace\", \"default\"),\n225:             \"image_url\": image_url,\n226:             \"status\": status.get(\"status\", \"running\") if status else \"unknown\",\n227:             \"endpoint\": status.get(\"agentEndpoint\") if status else None,\n228:             \"router_url\": metadata.router_url,\n229:             \"workload_manager_url\": metadata.workload_manager_url,\n230:         }\n231: \n232:     def _publish_k8s(self, workspace_path: Path, metadata: AgentMetadata, image_url: str, **options: Any) -> Dict[str, Any]:\n233:         \"\"\"Publish using standard Kubernetes Deployment/Service.\"\"\"\n234:         logger.info(\"Deploying standard Kubernetes Deployment and Service\")\n235: \n236:         provider = KubernetesProvider(\n237:             namespace=options.get(\"namespace\", \"default\"),\n238:             verbose=self.verbose,\n239:         )\n240: \n241:         # Prepare deployment config\n242:         replicas = options.get(\"replicas\", 1)\n243:         node_port = options.get(\"node_port\")\n244:         env_vars = self._build_agent_env_vars(metadata)\n245: \n246:         # Deploy\n247:         result = provider.deploy_agent(\n248:             agent_name=metadata.agent_name,\n249:             image_url=image_url,\n250:             port=metadata.port,\n251:             entrypoint=metadata.entrypoint,\n252:             replicas=replicas,\n253:             node_port=node_port,\n254:             env_vars=env_vars,\n255:         )\n256: \n257:         # Wait for deployment readiness\n258:         provider.wait_for_deployment_ready(metadata.agent_name, timeout=120)\n259: \n260:         # Get final status\n261:         status = provider.get_agent_status(metadata.agent_name)\n262: \n263:         return {\n264:             \"agent_name\": metadata.agent_name,\n265:             \"agent_id\": metadata.agent_name,\n266:             \"deployment_type\": \"Kubernetes\",\n267:             \"namespace\": options.get(\"namespace\", \"default\"),\n268:             \"image_url\": image_url,\n269:             \"deployment_name\": result[\"deployment_name\"],\n270:             \"service_name\": result[\"service_name\"],\n271:             \"node_port\": result[\"node_port\"],\n272:             \"service_url\": result[\"service_url\"],\n273:             \"replicas\": replicas,\n274:             \"status\": status.get(\"status\", \"running\") if status else \"unknown\",\n275:         }\n276: \n277:     def _prepare_image_for_publishing(self, workspace_path: Path, metadata: AgentMetadata, options: Dict[str, Any]) -> str:\n278:         \"\"\"Prepare container image for publishing.\"\"\"\n279:         # If image_url is provided, use it directly\n280:         if options.get(\"image_url\"):\n281:             logger.info(f\"Using provided image URL: {options['image_url']}\")\n282:             return options[\"image_url\"]\n283: \n284:         # For local build mode, build and push image\n285:         if metadata.build_mode == \"local\":\n286:             return self._prepare_local_image(workspace_path, metadata, options)\n287:         elif metadata.build_mode == \"cloud\":\n288:             return self._prepare_cloud_image(workspace_path, metadata, options)\n289:         else:\n290:             raise ValueError(f\"Unsupported build mode: {metadata.build_mode}\")\n291: \n292:     def _prepare_local_image(self, workspace_path: Path, metadata: AgentMetadata, options: Dict[str, Any]) -> str:\n293:         \"\"\"Prepare local Docker image.\"\"\"\n294:         logger.info(\"Building and pushing local Docker image\")\n295: \n296:         # Build image tag\n297:         tag = metadata.version or \"latest\"\n298:         image_name = f\"{metadata.agent_name}:{tag}\"\n299: \n300:         # Build Dockerfile path\n301:         dockerfile_path = workspace_path / \"Dockerfile\"\n302:         if not dockerfile_path.exists():\n303:             raise FileNotFoundError(f\"Dockerfile not found at {dockerfile_path}\")\n304: \n305:         # Build image\n306:         build_result = self.docker_service.build_image(\n307:             dockerfile_path=dockerfile_path,\n308:             context_path=workspace_path,\n309:             image_name=metadata.agent_name,\n310:             tag=tag,\n311:         )\n312: \n313:         logger.info(f\"Built image: {image_name} (ID: {build_result['image_id']})\")\n314: \n315:         # Push to registry if credentials provided\n316:         registry_url = options.get(\"registry_url\") or metadata.registry_url\n317:         username = options.get(\"image_username\") or metadata.registry_username\n318:         password = options.get(\"image_password\") or metadata.registry_password\n319: \n320:         if registry_url and username and password:\n321:             pushed_image = f\"{registry_url}/{image_name}\"\n322:             push_result = self.docker_service.push_image(\n323:                 image_name=image_name,\n324:                 registry_url=registry_url,\n325:                 username=username,\n326:                 password=password,\n327:             )\n328:             logger.info(f\"Pushed image to: {pushed_image}\")\n329:             return pushed_image\n330:         else:\n331:             logger.warning(\"Registry credentials not provided. Image built but not pushed.\")\n332:             return image_name\n333: \n334:     def _prepare_cloud_image(self, workspace_path: Path, metadata: AgentMetadata, options: Dict[str, Any]) -> str:\n335:         \"\"\"Prepare cloud-built image (requires external build service).\"\"\"\n336:         logger.info(\"Cloud build mode - expecting pre-built image\")\n337: \n338:         # In cloud mode, image should be provided or built by external service\n339:         if not options.get(\"image_url\"):\n340:             raise ValueError(\n341:                 \"Cloud build mode requires --image-url to specify the pre-built image\"\n342:             )\n343: \n344:         return options[\"image_url\"]\n345: \n346:     def _build_agent_env_vars(self, metadata: AgentMetadata) -> Dict[str, str]:\n347:         \"\"\"Build environment variables for agent deployment.\"\"\"\n348:         env_vars: Dict[str, str] = {}\n349: \n350:         # Add metadata fields as env vars\n351:         if metadata.workload_manager_url:\n352:             env_vars[\"WORKLOAD_MANAGER_URL\"] = metadata.workload_manager_url\n353:         if metadata.router_url:\n354:             env_vars[\"ROUTER_URL\"] = metadata.router_url\n355:         if metadata.agent_endpoint:\n356:             env_vars[\"AGENT_ENDPOINT\"] = metadata.agent_endpoint\n357: \n358:         return env_vars\n359: \n360:     def _update_publish_metadata(self, workspace_path: Path, agent_info: Dict[str, Any]) -> None:\n361:         \"\"\"Update metadata after publishing.\"\"\"\n362:         metadata = self.metadata_service.load_metadata(workspace_path)\n363: \n364:         # Update fields from agent_info\n365:         updates = {\n366:             \"agent_id\": agent_info.get(\"agent_id\"),\n367:             \"agent_endpoint\": agent_info.get(\"endpoint\") or agent_info.get(\"service_url\"),\n368:             \"image\": {\n369:                 \"url\": agent_info.get(\"image_url\"),\n370:                 \"type\": agent_info.get(\"deployment_type\"),\n371:             },\n372:             \"k8s_deployment\": {\n373:                 \"type\": agent_info.get(\"deployment_type\"),\n374:                 \"namespace\": agent_info.get(\"namespace\"),\n375:                 \"name\": agent_info.get(\"deployment_name\") or agent_info.get(\"agent_name\"),\n376:             },\n377:         }\n378: \n379:         # Merge updates\n380:         metadata_dict = metadata.model_dump()\n381:         for key, value in updates.items():\n382:             if value is not None:\n383:                 metadata_dict[key] = value\n384: \n385:         updated_metadata = AgentMetadata(**metadata_dict)\n386:         self.metadata_service.save_metadata(workspace_path, updated_metadata)\n387:         logger.debug(\"Updated publish metadata\")\n388: ```\n389: \n390: ### 2. AgentCubeProvider Implementation\n391: \n392: ```python\n393: # agentcube/services/agentcube_provider.py\n394: \"\"\"AgentCubeProvider for AgentRuntime CR operations.\"\"\"\n395: \n396: from __future__ import annotations\n397: \n398: import logging\n399: import time\n400: from typing import Any, Dict, List, Optional\n401: \n402: logger = logging.getLogger(__name__)\n403: \n404: try:\n405:     from kubernetes import client, config\n406:     from kubernetes.client.rest import ApiException\n407:     K8S_AVAILABLE = True\n408: except ImportError:\n409:     K8S_AVAILABLE = False\n410:     logger.warning(\"Kubernetes client not available. Install with: pip install kubernetes\")\n411: \n412: \n413: class AgentCubeProvider:\n414:     \"\"\"Provider for AgentCube AgentRuntime CR operations.\"\"\"\n415: \n416:     API_GROUP = \"runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh\"\n417:     API_VERSION = \"v1alpha1\"\n418:     CR_PLURAL = \"agentruntimes\"\n419: \n420:     def __init__(\n421:         self,\n422:         namespace: str = \"default\",\n423:         verbose: bool = False,\n424:         kubeconfig: Optional[str] = None,\n425:     ) -> None:\n426:         self.namespace = namespace\n427:         self.verbose = verbose\n428:         self.kubeconfig = kubeconfig\n429: \n430:         if not K8S_AVAILABLE:\n431:             raise ImportError(\"Kubernetes client not available. Install with: pip install kubernetes\")\n432: \n433:         # Initialize Kubernetes client\n434:         try:\n435:             if kubeconfig:\n436:                 config.load_kube_config(config_file=kubeconfig)\n437:             else:\n438:                 config.load_incluster_config()\n439:         except config.ConfigException:\n440:             logger.warning(\"Failed to load Kubernetes config, attempting default config\")\n441:             config.load_kube_config()\n442: \n443:         self.api_client = client.ApiClient()\n444:         self.custom_objects_api = client.CustomObjectsApi(self.api_client)\n445: \n446:         if verbose:\n447:             logging.basicConfig(level=logging.DEBUG)\n448: \n449:     def _ensure_namespace(self) -> None:\n450:         \"\"\"Ensure namespace exists.\"\"\"\n451:         core_v1 = client.CoreV1Api()\n452:         try:\n453:             core_v1.read_namespace(self.namespace)\n454:             logger.debug(f\"Namespace {self.namespace} exists\")\n455:         except ApiException as e:\n456:             if e.status == 404:\n457:                 logger.info(f\"Creating namespace: {self.namespace}\")\n458:                 namespace_obj = client.V1Namespace(\n459:                     metadata=client.V1ObjectMeta(name=self.namespace)\n460:                 )\n461:                 core_v1.create_namespace(namespace_obj)\n462:             else:\n463:                 raise\n464: \n465:     def deploy_agent_runtime(\n466:         self,\n467:         agent_name: str,\n468:         image_url: str,\n469:         port: int,\n470:         entrypoint: Optional[str] = None,\n471:         env_vars: Optional[Dict[str, str]] = None,\n472:         workload_manager_url: Optional[str] = None,\n473:         router_url: Optional[str] = None,\n474:         readiness_probe_path: Optional[str] = None,\n475:         readiness_probe_port: Optional[int] = None,\n476:     ) -> Dict[str, Any]:\n477:         \"\"\"Deploy an AgentRuntime CR.\"\"\"\n478:         logger.info(f\"Deploying AgentRuntime CR: {agent_name}\")\n479: \n480:         # Ensure namespace exists\n481:         self._ensure_namespace()\n482: \n483:         # Sanitize name for Kubernetes\n484:         sanitized_name = self._sanitize_name(agent_name)\n485: \n486:         # Build environment variables\n487:         container_env: List[Dict[str, str]] = []\n488: \n489:         # Add required AgentCube env vars\n490:         if workload_manager_url:\n491:             container_env.append({\"name\": \"WORKLOAD_MANAGER_URL\", \"value\": workload_manager_url})\n492:         elif \"WORKLOAD_MANAGER_URL\" not in (env_vars or {}):\n493:             # Try from environment\n494:             import os\n495:             if os.getenv(\"WORKLOAD_MANAGER_URL\"):\n496:                 container_env.append({\"name\": \"WORKLOAD_MANAGER_URL\", \"value\": os.getenv(\"WORKLOAD_MANAGER_URL\")})\n497: \n498:         if router_url:\n499:             container_env.append({\"name\": \"ROUTER_URL\", \"value\": router_url})\n500:         elif \"ROUTER_URL\" not in (env_vars or {}):\n501:             import os\n502:             if os.getenv(\"ROUTER_URL\"):\n503:                 container_env.append({\"name\": \"ROUTER_URL\", \"value\": os.getenv(\"ROUTER_URL\")})\n504: \n505:         # Add user-provided env vars\n506:         if env_vars:\n507:             for key, value in env_vars.items():\n508:                 if key not in [\"WORKLOAD_MANAGER_URL\", \"ROUTER_URL\"]:\n509:                     container_env.append({\"name\": key, \"value\": value})\n510: \n511:         # Build AgentRuntime CR object\n512:         cr_object = {\n513:             \"apiVersion\": f\"{self.API_GROUP}/{self.API_VERSION}\",\n514:             \"kind\": \"AgentRuntime\",\n515:             \"metadata\": {\n516:                 \"name\": sanitized_name,\n517:                 \"namespace\": self.namespace,\n518:             },\n519:             \"spec\": {\n520:                 \"agentName\": agent_name,\n521:                 \"image\": image_url,\n522:                 \"port\": port,\n523:                 \"entrypoint\": entrypoint or f\"python main.py\",\n524:                 \"sessionTimeout\": \"15m\",\n525:                 \"maxSessionDuration\": \"8h\",\n526:                 \"imagePullSecrets\": [{\"name\": \"default-secret\"}],\n527:                 \"readinessProbe\": {\n528:                     \"httpGet\": {\n529:                         \"path\": readiness_probe_path or \"/health\",\n530:                         \"port\": readiness_probe_port or port,\n531:                     },\n532:                     \"initialDelaySeconds\": 5,\n533:                     \"periodSeconds\": 10,\n534:                     \"timeoutSeconds\": 5,\n535:                     \"failureThreshold\": 3,\n536:                 },\n537:                 \"env\": container_env if container_env else None,\n538:             },\n539:         }\n540: \n541:         # Remove None fields\n542:         cr_object[\"spec\"] = {k: v for k, v in cr_object[\"spec\"].items() if v is not None}\n543:         if cr_object[\"spec\"].get(\"env\") is None:\n544:             del cr_object[\"spec\"][\"env\"]\n545: \n546:         # Check if CR already exists\n547:         try:\n548:             existing = self.get_agent_runtime(sanitized_name, self.namespace)\n549:             if existing:\n550:                 logger.info(f\"Updating existing AgentRuntime: {sanitized_name}\")\n551:                 # Update existing CR\n552:                 cr_object[\"metadata\"][\"resourceVersion\"] = existing.get(\"metadata\", {}).get(\"resourceVersion\", \"\")\n553:                 result = self.custom_objects_api.patch_namespaced_custom_object(\n554:                     group=self.API_GROUP,\n555:                     version=self.API_VERSION,\n556:                     namespace=self.namespace,\n557:                     plural=self.CR_PLURAL,\n558:                     name=sanitized_name,\n559:                     body=cr_object,\n560:                 )\n561:             else:\n562:                 logger.info(f\"Creating new AgentRuntime: {sanitized_name}\")\n563:                 result = self.custom_objects_api.create_namespaced_custom_object(\n564:                     group=self.API_GROUP,\n565:                     version=self.API_VERSION,\n566:                     namespace=self.namespace,\n567:                     plural=self.CR_PLURAL,\n568:                     body=cr_object,\n569:                 )\n570:         except ApiException as e:\n571:             logger.error(f\"Failed to deploy AgentRuntime: {e}\")\n572:             raise\n573: \n574:         logger.info(f\"AgentRuntime deployed: {sanitized_name}\")\n575: \n576:         return {\n577:             \"agent_name\": agent_name,\n578:             \"cr_name\": sanitized_name,\n579:             \"namespace\": self.namespace,\n580:             \"image_url\": image_url,\n581:             \"port\": port,\n582:         }\n583: \n584:     def _sanitize_name(self, name: str) -> str:\n585:         \"\"\"Sanitize name for Kubernetes resource.\"\"\"\n586:         # Kubernetes names must be lowercase, max 63 chars, alphanumeric + hyphen\n587:         sanitized = name.lower().replace(\"_\", \"-\").replace(\".\", \"-\")\n588:         sanitized = \"\".join(c for c in sanitized if c.isalnum() or c == \"-\")\n589:         # Remove leading/trailing hyphens\n590:         sanitized = sanitized.strip(\"-\")\n591:         # Truncate to 63 chars\n592:         if len(sanitized) > 63:\n593:             sanitized = sanitized[:63]\n594:         return sanitized\n595: \n596:     def get_agent_runtime(self, name: str, namespace: str) -> Optional[Dict[str, Any]]:\n597:         \"\"\"Get an AgentRuntime CR.\"\"\"\n598:         try:\n599:             result = self.custom_objects_api.get_namespaced_custom_object(\n600:                 group=self.API_GROUP,\n601:                 version=self.API_VERSION,\n602:                 namespace=namespace,\n603:                 plural=self.CR_PLURAL,\n604:                 name=name,\n605:             )\n606:             return result\n607:         except ApiException as e:\n608:             if e.status == 404:\n609:                 logger.debug(f\"AgentRuntime not found: {name}\")\n610:                 return None\n611:             raise\n612: \n613:     def wait_for_deployment_ready(self, agent_name: str, timeout: int = 120) -> None:\n614:         \"\"\"Wait for AgentRuntime to be ready.\"\"\"\n615:         logger.info(f\"Waiting for AgentRuntime {agent_name} to be ready (timeout: {timeout}s)\")\n616: \n617:         start_time = time.time()\n618:         sanitized_name = self._sanitize_name(agent_name)\n619: \n620:         while time.time() - start_time < timeout:\n621:             try:\n622:                 cr = self.get_agent_runtime(sanitized_name, self.namespace)\n623:                 if cr:\n624:                     status = cr.get(\"status\", {})\n625:                     phase = status.get(\"phase\", \"\")\n626:                     conditions = status.get(\"conditions\", [])\n627: \n628:                     # Check for ready condition\n629:                     for condition in conditions:\n630:                         if condition.get(\"type\") == \"Ready\" and condition.get(\"status\") == \"True\":\n631:                             logger.info(f\"AgentRuntime {agent_name} is ready\")\n632:                             return\n633: \n634:                     logger.debug(f\"AgentRuntime status: {phase}\")\n635: \n636:             except ApiException as e:\n637:                 logger.warning(f\"Error checking AgentRuntime status: {e}\")\n638: \n639:             time.sleep(5)\n640: \n641:         raise TimeoutError(f\"AgentRuntime {agent_name} did not become ready within {timeout}s\")\n642: \n643:     def get_agent_runtime_status(self, agent_name: str) -> Dict[str, Any]:\n644:         \"\"\"Get AgentRuntime status.\"\"\"\n645:         sanitized_name = self._sanitize_name(agent_name)\n646:         cr = self.get_agent_runtime(sanitized_name, self.namespace)\n647: \n648:         if not cr:\n649:             return {\"status\": \"not_found\", \"agent_name\": agent_name}\n650: \n651:         status = cr.get(\"status\", {})\n652:         return {\n653:             \"status\": status.get(\"phase\", \"unknown\"),\n654:             \"agent_name\": agent_name,\n655:             \"cr_name\": sanitized_name,\n656:             \"namespace\": self.namespace,\n657:             \"agent_endpoint\": status.get(\"agentEndpoint\"),\n658:             \"conditions\": status.get(\"conditions\", []),\n659:         }\n660: \n661:     def delete_agent_runtime(self, agent_name: str) -> Dict[str, Any]:\n662:         \"\"\"Delete an AgentRuntime CR.\"\"\"\n663:         sanitized_name = self._sanitize_name(agent_name)\n664:         logger.info(f\"Deleting AgentRuntime: {sanitized_name}\")\n665: \n666:         try:\n667:             self.custom_objects_api.delete_namespaced_custom_object(\n668:                 group=self.API_GROUP,\n669:                 version=self.API_VERSION,\n670:                 namespace=self.namespace,\n671:                 plural=self.CR_PLURAL,\n672:                 name=sanitized_name,\n673:             )\n674:             logger.info(f\"AgentRuntime deleted: {sanitized_name}\")\n675:             return {\"status\": \"deleted\", \"agent_name\": agent_name, \"namespace\": self.namespace}\n676:         except ApiException as e:\n677:             if e.status == 404:\n678:                 logger.warning(f\"AgentRuntime not found: {sanitized_name}\")\n679:                 return {\"status\": \"not_found\", \"agent_name\": agent_name}\n680:             raise\n681: ```\n682: \n683: ### 3. KubernetesProvider Implementation\n684: \n685: ```python\n686: # agentcube/services/k8s_provider.py\n687: \"\"\"KubernetesProvider for standard K8s Deployment/Service operations.\"\"\"\n688: \n689: from __future__ import annotations\n690: \n691: import logging\n692: import time\n693: from typing import Any, Dict, List, Optional\n694: \n695: logger = logging.getLogger(__name__)\n696: \n697: try:\n698:     from kubernetes import client, config\n699:     from kubernetes.client.rest import ApiException\n700:     K8S_AVAILABLE = True\n701: except ImportError:\n702:     K8S_AVAILABLE = False\n703:     logger.warning(\"Kubernetes client not available. Install with: pip install kubernetes\")\n704: \n705: \n706: class KubernetesProvider:\n707:     \"\"\"Provider for standard Kubernetes operations.\"\"\"\n708: \n709:     def __init__(\n710:         self,\n711:         namespace: str = \"default\",\n712:         verbose: bool = False,\n713:         kubeconfig: Optional[str] = None,\n714:     ) -> None:\n715:         self.namespace = namespace\n716:         self.verbose = verbose\n717:         self.kubeconfig = kubeconfig\n718: \n719:         if not K8S_AVAILABLE:\n720:             raise ImportError(\"Kubernetes client not available. Install with: pip install kubernetes\")\n721: \n722:         # Initialize Kubernetes clients\n723:         try:\n724:             if kubeconfig:\n725:                 config.load_kube_config(config_file=kubeconfig)\n726:             else:\n727:                 config.load_incluster_config()\n728:         except config.ConfigException:\n729:             logger.warning(\"Failed to load Kubernetes config, attempting default config\")\n730:             config.load_kube_config()\n731: \n732:         self.apps_v1 = client.AppsV1Api()\n733:         self.core_v1 = client.CoreV1Api()\n734: \n735:         if verbose:\n736:             logging.basicConfig(level=logging.DEBUG)\n737: \n738:     def _ensure_namespace(self) -> None:\n739:         \"\"\"Ensure namespace exists.\"\"\"\n740:         try:\n741:             self.core_v1.read_namespace(self.namespace)\n742:             logger.debug(f\"Namespace {self.namespace} exists\")\n743:         except ApiException as e:\n744:             if e.status == 404:\n745:                 logger.info(f\"Creating namespace: {self.namespace}\")\n746:                 namespace_obj = client.V1Namespace(\n747:                     metadata=client.V1ObjectMeta(name=self.namespace)\n748:                 )\n749:                 self.core_v1.create_namespace(namespace_obj)\n750:             else:\n751:                 raise\n752: \n753:     def deploy_agent(\n754:         self,\n755:         agent_name: str,\n756:         image_url: str,\n757:         port: int,\n758:         entrypoint: Optional[str] = None,\n759:         replicas: int = 1,\n760:         node_port: Optional[int] = None,\n761:         env_vars: Optional[Dict[str, str]] = None,\n762:     ) -> Dict[str, Any]:\n763:         \"\"\"Deploy a standard Kubernetes Deployment and Service.\"\"\"\n764:         logger.info(f\"Deploying agent: {agent_name}\")\n765: \n766:         # Ensure namespace exists\n767:         self._ensure_namespace()\n768: \n769:         # Sanitize name\n770:         sanitized_name = self._sanitize_name(agent_name)\n771: \n772:         # Create deployment\n773:         deployment_result = self._create_deployment(\n774:             name=sanitized_name,\n775:             image_url=image_url,\n776:             port=port,\n777:             entrypoint=entrypoint,\n778:             replicas=replicas,\n779:             env_vars=env_vars,\n780:         )\n781: \n782:         # Create service\n783:         service_result = self._create_service(\n784:             name=sanitized_name,\n785:             port=port,\n786:             node_port=node_port,\n787:         )\n788: \n789:         logger.info(f\"Agent deployed: {sanitized_name}\")\n790: \n791:         return {\n792:             \"agent_name\": agent_name,\n793:             \"deployment_name\": deployment_result[\"deployment_name\"],\n794:             \"service_name\": service_result[\"service_name\"],\n795:             \"namespace\": self.namespace,\n796:             \"replicas\": replicas,\n797:             \"container_port\": port,\n798:             \"node_port\": service_result[\"node_port\"],\n799:             \"service_url\": service_result[\"service_url\"],\n800:         }\n801: \n802:     def _create_deployment(\n803:         self,\n804:         name: str,\n805:         image_url: str,\n806:         port: int,\n807:         entrypoint: Optional[str],\n808:         replicas: int,\n809:         env_vars: Optional[Dict[str, str]],\n810:     ) -> Dict[str, Any]:\n811:         \"\"\"Create Kubernetes Deployment.\"\"\"\n812:         logger.debug(f\"Creating deployment: {name}\")\n813: \n814:         # Build container env\n815:         container_env: List[client.V1EnvVar] = []\n816:         if env_vars:\n817:             for key, value in env_vars.items():\n818:                 container_env.append(client.V1EnvVar(name=key, value=value))\n819: \n820:         # Build container\n821:         container = client.V1Container(\n822:             name=name,\n823:             image=image_url,\n824:             ports=[client.V1ContainerPort(container_port=port)],\n825:             env=container_env if container_env else None,\n826:         )\n827: \n828:         # Add entrypoint if provided\n829:         if entrypoint:\n830:             # Parse entrypoint command\n831:             import shlex\n832:             container.command = shlex.split(entrypoint)\n833: \n834:         # Build pod spec\n835:         pod_spec = client.V1PodSpec(\n836:             containers=[container],\n837:         )\n838: \n839:         # Build pod template\n840:         pod_template = client.V1PodTemplateSpec(\n841:             metadata=client.V1ObjectMeta(labels={\"app\": name}),\n842:             spec=pod_spec,\n843:         )\n844: \n845:         # Build deployment spec\n846:         deployment_spec = client.V1DeploymentSpec(\n847:             replicas=replicas,\n848:             selector=client.V1LabelSelector(match_labels={\"app\": name}),\n849:             template=pod_template,\n850:         )\n851: \n852:         # Build deployment\n853:         deployment = client.V1Deployment(\n854:             api_version=\"apps/v1\",\n855:             kind=\"Deployment\",\n856:             metadata=client.V1ObjectMeta(name=name, namespace=self.namespace),\n857:             spec=deployment_spec,\n858:         )\n859: \n860:         # Create or update deployment\n861:         try:\n862:             existing = self.apps_v1.read_namespaced_deployment(name, self.namespace)\n863:             if existing:\n864:                 logger.info(f\"Updating existing deployment: {name}\")\n865:                 result = self.apps_v1.patch_namespaced_deployment(name, self.namespace, deployment)\n866:             else:\n867:                 logger.info(f\"Creating new deployment: {name}\")\n868:                 result = self.apps_v1.create_namespaced_deployment(self.namespace, deployment)\n869:         except ApiException as e:\n870:             logger.error(f\"Failed to create deployment: {e}\")\n871:             raise\n872: \n873:         return {\n874:             \"deployment_name\": name,\n875:             \"namespace\": self.namespace,\n876:             \"replicas\": replicas,\n877:         }\n878: \n879:     def _create_service(self, name: str, port: int, node_port: Optional[int]) -> Dict[str, Any]:\n880:         \"\"\"Create Kubernetes NodePort Service.\"\"\"\n881:         logger.debug(f\"Creating service: {name}\")\n882: \n883:         # Determine service type\n884:         if node_port:\n885:             service_type = \"NodePort\"\n886:         else:\n887:             # Auto-assign NodePort\n888:             service_type = \"NodePort\"\n889:             node_port = None  # Let K8s assign\n890: \n891:         # Build service port\n892:         service_port = client.V1ServicePort(\n893:             port=port,\n894:             target_port=port,\n895:             node_port=node_port,\n896:         )\n897: \n898:         # Build service spec\n899:         service_spec = client.V1ServiceSpec(\n900:             type=service_type,\n901:             selector={\"app\": name},\n902:             ports=[service_port],\n903:         )\n904: \n905:         # Build service\n906:         service = client.V1Service(\n907:             api_version=\"v1\",\n908:             kind=\"Service\",\n909:             metadata=client.V1ObjectMeta(name=name, namespace=self.namespace),\n910:             spec=service_spec,\n911:         )\n912: \n913:         # Create service\n914:         try:\n915:             result = self.core_v1.create_namespaced_service(self.namespace, service)\n916:             actual_node_port = result.spec.ports[0].node_port\n917:             logger.info(f\"Service created with NodePort: {actual_node_port}\")\n918:             return {\n919:                 \"service_name\": name,\n920:                 \"namespace\": self.namespace,\n921:                 \"node_port\": actual_node_port,\n922:                 \"service_url\": f\"http://localhost:{actual_node_port}\",\n923:             }\n924:         except ApiException as e:\n925:             logger.error(f\"Failed to create service: {e}\")\n926:             raise\n927: \n928:     def wait_for_deployment_ready(self, name: str, timeout: int = 120) -> None:\n929:         \"\"\"Wait for Deployment to be ready.\"\"\"\n930:         logger.info(f\"Waiting for deployment {name} to be ready (timeout: {timeout}s)\")\n931: \n932:         start_time = time.time()\n933: \n934:         while time.time() - start_time < timeout:\n935:             try:\n936:                 deployment = self.apps_v1.read_namespaced_deployment(name, self.namespace)\n937:                 status = deployment.status\n938: \n939:                 # Check readiness\n940:                 ready_replicas = status.ready_replicas or 0\n941:                 desired_replicas = status.replicas or 0\n942: \n943:                 if ready_replicas == desired_replicas and ready_replicas > 0:\n944:                     logger.info(f\"Deployment {name} is ready ({ready_replicas}/{desired_replicas})\")\n945:                     return\n946: \n947:                 logger.debug(f\"Deployment status: {ready_replicas}/{desired_replicas} ready\")\n948: \n949:             except ApiException as e:\n950:                 logger.warning(f\"Error checking deployment status: {e}\")\n951: \n952:             time.sleep(5)\n953: \n954:         raise TimeoutError(f\"Deployment {name} did not become ready within {timeout}s\")\n955: \n956:     def get_agent_status(self, agent_name: str) -> Dict[str, Any]:\n957:         \"\"\"Get agent deployment status.\"\"\"\n958:         sanitized_name = self._sanitize_name(agent_name)\n959: \n960:         try:\n961:             deployment = self.apps_v1.read_namespaced_deployment(sanitized_name, self.namespace)\n962:             service = self.core_v1.read_namespaced_service(sanitized_name, self.namespace)\n963: \n964:             status = deployment.status\n965:             ready_replicas = status.ready_replicas or 0\n966:             desired_replicas = status.replicas or 0\n967: \n968:             node_port = service.spec.ports[0].node_port if service.spec.ports else None\n969: \n970:             return {\n971:                 \"status\": \"running\" if ready_replicas == desired_replicas else \"pending\",\n972:                 \"agent_name\": agent_name,\n973:                 \"deployment_name\": sanitized_name,\n974:                 \"namespace\": self.namespace,\n975:                 \"ready_replicas\": ready_replicas,\n976:                 \"desired_replicas\": desired_replicas,\n977:                 \"node_port\": node_port,\n978:                 \"service_url\": f\"http://localhost:{node_port}\" if node_port else None,\n979:             }\n980:         except ApiException as e:\n981:             if e.status == 404:\n982:                 return {\"status\": \"not_found\", \"agent_name\": agent_name}\n983:             raise\n984: \n985:     def delete_agent(self, agent_name: str) -> Dict[str, Any]:\n986:         \"\"\"Delete agent Deployment and Service.\"\"\"\n987:         sanitized_name = self._sanitize_name(agent_name)\n988:         logger.info(f\"Deleting agent: {sanitized_name}\")\n989: \n990:         results = {\"status\": \"deleted\", \"deployment_name\": sanitized_name, \"namespace\": self.namespace}\n991: \n992:         # Delete deployment\n993:         try:\n994:             self.apps_v1.delete_namespaced_deployment(sanitized_name, self.namespace)\n995:             logger.info(f\"Deployment deleted: {sanitized_name}\")\n996:         except ApiException as e:\n997:             if e.status != 404:\n998:                 raise\n999:             results[\"deployment_status\"] = \"not_found\"\n1000: \n1001:         # Delete service\n1002:         try:\n1003:             self.core_v1.delete_namespaced_service(sanitized_name, self.namespace)\n1004:             logger.info(f\"Service deleted: {sanitized_name}\")\n1005:         except ApiException as e:\n1006:             if e.status != 404:\n1007:                 raise\n1008:             results[\"service_status\"] = \"not_found\"\n1009: \n1010:         return results\n1011: \n1012:     def _sanitize_name(self, name: str) -> str:\n1013:         \"\"\"Sanitize name for Kubernetes resource.\"\"\"\n1014:         # Kubernetes names must be lowercase, max 63 chars, alphanumeric + hyphen\n1015:         sanitized = name.lower().replace(\"_\", \"-\").replace(\".\", \"-\")\n1016:         sanitized = \"\".join(c for c in sanitized if c.isalnum() or c == \"-\")\n1017:         sanitized = sanitized.strip(\"-\")\n1018:         if len(sanitized) > 63:\n1019:             sanitized = sanitized[:63]\n1020:         return sanitized\n1021: ```\n1022: \n1023: ### 4. DockerService Enhancement\n1024: \n1025: ```python\n1026: # agentcube/services/docker_service.py\n1027: \"\"\"DockerService for Docker operations.\"\"\"\n1028: \n1029: from __future__ import annotations\n1030: \n1031: import logging\n1032: from pathlib import Path\n1033: from typing import Any, Dict, Optional\n1034: \n1035: logger = logging.getLogger(__name__)\n1036: \n1037: try:\n1038:     import docker\n1039:     from docker.errors import DockerException, APIError\n1040:     DOCKER_AVAILABLE = True\n1041: except ImportError:\n1042:     DOCKER_AVAILABLE = False\n1043:     logger.warning(\"Docker SDK not available. Install with: pip install docker\")\n1044: \n1045: \n1046: class DockerService:\n1047:     \"\"\"Service for Docker operations.\"\"\"\n1048: \n1049:     def __init__(self, verbose: bool = False) -> None:\n1050:         self.verbose = verbose\n1051:         self.client: Optional[docker.DockerClient] = None\n1052: \n1053:         if not DOCKER_AVAILABLE:\n1054:             raise ImportError(\"Docker SDK not available. Install with: pip install docker\")\n1055: \n1056:         try:\n1057:             self.client = docker.from_env()\n1058:             if verbose:\n1059:                 logger.debug(\"Docker client initialized\")\n1060:         except DockerException as e:\n1061:             logger.warning(f\"Docker not available: {e}\")\n1062:             self.client = None\n1063: \n1064:         if verbose:\n1065:             logging.basicConfig(level=logging.DEBUG)\n1066: \n1067:     def check_docker_available(self) -> bool:\n1068:         \"\"\"Check if Docker is available.\"\"\"\n1069:         if self.client is None:\n1070:             return False\n1071:         try:\n1072:             self.client.ping()\n1073:             return True\n1074:         except DockerException:\n1075:             return False\n1076: \n1077:     def build_image(\n1078:         self,\n1079:         dockerfile_path: Path,\n1080:         context_path: Path,\n1081:         image_name: str,\n1082:         tag: str = \"latest\",\n1083:         build_args: Optional[Dict[str, str]] = None,\n1084:     ) -> Dict[str, str]:\n1085:         \"\"\"Build a Docker image.\"\"\"\n1086:         import time\n1087:         start_time = time.time()\n1088: \n1089:         logger.info(f\"Building image {image_name}:{tag} from {dockerfile_path}\")\n1090: \n1091:         if self.client is None:\n1092:             raise DockerException(\"Docker client not initialized\")\n1093: \n1094:         try:\n1095:             image, build_logs = self.client.images.build(\n1096:                 path=str(context_path),\n1097:                 dockerfile=str(dockerfile_path),\n1098:                 tag=f\"{image_name}:{tag}\",\n1099:                 buildargs=build_args or {},\n1100:                 rm=True,\n1101:                 pull=False,\n1102:             )\n1103: \n1104:             build_time = time.time() - start_time\n1105: \n1106:             # Get image info\n1107:             image_info = self.get_image_info(image_name)\n1108: \n1109:             logger.info(f\"Image built successfully: {image_name}:{tag}\")\n1110: \n1111:             return {\n1112:                 \"image_name\": image_name,\n1113:                 \"tag\": tag,\n1114:                 \"image_id\": image.short_id,\n1115:                 \"image_size\": image_info.get(\"image_size\", \"unknown\"),\n1116:                 \"build_time\": f\"{build_time:.2f}s\",\n1117:             }\n1118: \n1119:         except APIError as e:\n1120:             logger.error(f\"Docker build failed: {e}\")\n1121:             raise\n1122:         except Exception as e:\n1123:             logger.error(f\"Build error: {e}\")\n1124:             raise\n1125: \n1126:     def get_image_info(self, image_name: str) -> Dict[str, str]:\n1127:         \"\"\"Get image information.\"\"\"\n1128:         return self._get_image_info(image_name)\n1129: \n1130:     def _get_image_info(self, image_name: str) -> Dict[str, str]:\n1131:         \"\"\"Get image details.\"\"\"\n1132:         if self.client is None:\n1133:             raise DockerException(\"Docker client not initialized\")\n1134: \n1135:         try:\n1136:             image = self.client.images.get(image_name)\n1137:             attrs = image.attrs\n1138:             return {\n1139:                 \"image_name\": image_name,\n1140:                 \"image_id\": image.short_id,\n1141:                 \"image_size\": self._format_size(attrs.get(\"Size\", 0)),\n1142:                 \"created\": attrs.get(\"Created\", \"unknown\"),\n1143:             }\n1144:         except APIError as e:\n1145:             logger.error(f\"Failed to get image info: {e}\")\n1146:             return {\"image_name\": image_name, \"error\": str(e)}\n1147: \n1148:     def _format_size(self, size_bytes: int) -> str:\n1149:         \"\"\"Format size in human-readable format.\"\"\"\n1150:         for unit in [\"B\", \"KB\", \"MB\", \"GB\"]:\n1151:             if size_bytes < 1024:\n1152:                 return f\"{size_bytes:.2f} {unit}\"\n1153:             size_bytes /= 1024\n1154:         return f\"{size_bytes:.2f} TB\"\n1155: \n1156:     def push_image(\n1157:         self,\n1158:         image_name: str,\n1159:         registry_url: Optional[str] = None,\n1160:         username: Optional[str] = None,\n1161:         password: Optional[str] = None,\n1162:     ) -> Dict[str, str]:\n1163:         \"\"\"Push image to registry.\"\"\"\n1164:         import time\n1165:         start_time = time.time()\n1166: \n1167:         logger.info(f\"Pushing image {image_name} to {registry_url or 'Docker Hub'}\")\n1168: \n1169:         if self.client is None:\n1170:             raise DockerException(\"Docker client not initialized\")\n1171: \n1172:         # Login if credentials provided\n1173:         if username and password:\n1174:             self._docker_login(registry_url, username, password)\n1175: \n1176:         # Tag image if registry URL provided\n1177:         if registry_url:\n1178:             target_image = f\"{registry_url}/{image_name}\"\n1179:             logger.info(f\"Tagging image: {target_image}\")\n1180:             self._tag_image(image_name, target_image)\n1181:             push_image_name = target_image\n1182:         else:\n1183:             push_image_name = image_name\n1184: \n1185:         try:\n1186:             # Push image\n1187:             push_logs = self.client.images.push(push_image_name)\n1188: \n1189:             push_time = time.time() - start_time\n1190: \n1191:             logger.info(f\"Image pushed successfully: {push_image_name}\")\n1192: \n1193:             return {\n1194:                 \"pushed_image\": push_image_name,\n1195:                 \"push_time\": f\"{push_time:.2f}s\",\n1196:                 \"logs\": push_logs,\n1197:             }\n1198: \n1199:         except APIError as e:\n1200:             logger.error(f\"Push failed: {e}\")\n1201:             raise\n1202: \n1203:     def _docker_login(self, registry: Optional[str], username: str, password: str) -> None:\n1204:         \"\"\"Login to Docker registry.\"\"\"\n1205:         if self.client is None:\n1206:             raise DockerException(\"Docker client not initialized\")\n1207: \n1208:         registry_url = registry or \"https://index.docker.io/v1/\"\n1209:         logger.debug(f\"Logging in to registry: {registry_url}\")\n1210: \n1211:         try:\n1212:             self.client.login(\n1213:                 username=username,\n1214:                 password=password,\n1215:                 registry=registry_url,\n1216:             )\n1217:             logger.debug(\"Docker login successful\")\n1218:         except APIError as e:\n1219:             logger.error(f\"Docker login failed: {e}\")\n1220:             raise\n1221: \n1222:     def _tag_image(self, source_image: str, target_image: str) -> None:\n1223:         \"\"\"Tag image.\"\"\"\n1224:         if self.client is None:\n1225:             raise DockerException(\"Docker client not initialized\")\n1226: \n1227:         try:\n1228:             image = self.client.images.get(source_image)\n1229:             image.tag(target_image)\n1230:             logger.debug(f\"Tagged {source_image} as {target_image}\")\n1231:         except APIError as e:\n1232:             logger.error(f\"Tag failed: {e}\")\n1233:             raise\n1234: \n1235:     def remove_image(self, image_name: str) -> bool:\n1236:         \"\"\"Remove Docker image.\"\"\"\n1237:         if self.client is None:\n1238:             logger.warning(\"Docker client not initialized\")\n1239:             return False\n1240: \n1241:         try:\n1242:             self.client.images.remove(image_name, force=True)\n1243:             logger.info(f\"Image removed: {image_name}\")\n1244:             return True\n1245:         except APIError as e:\n1246:             logger.warning(f\"Failed to remove image: {e}\")\n1247:             return False\n1248: ```\n1249: \n1250: ### 5. CLI Publish Command\n1251: \n1252: ```python\n1253: # agentcube/cli/main.py (add publish command)\n1254: \n1255: @app.command()\n1256: def publish(\n1257:     workspace: str = typer.Option(\".\", \"-f\", \"--workspace\", help=\"Path to the agent workspace directory\", show_default=True),\n1258:     version: Optional[str] = typer.Option(None, \"--version\", help=\"Semantic version string (e.g., v1.0.0)\"),\n1259:     image_url: Optional[str] = typer.Option(None, \"--image-url\", help=\"Image repository URL (required in local build mode)\"),\n1260:     image_username: Optional[str] = typer.Option(None, \"--image-username\", help=\"Username for image repository\"),\n1261:     image_password: Optional[str] = typer.Option(None, \"--image-password\", help=\"Password for image repository\"),\n1262:     description: Optional[str] = typer.Option(None, \"--description\", help=\"Agent description\"),\n1263:     region: Optional[str] = typer.Option(None, \"--region\", help=\"Deployment region\"),\n1264:     cloud_provider: Optional[str] = typer.Option(None, \"--cloud-provider\", help=\"Cloud provider name (e.g., huawei)\"),\n1265:     provider: str = typer.Option(\"agentcube\", \"--provider\", help=\"Target provider: 'agentcube' (AgentRuntime CR) or 'k8s' (Deployment/Service)\"),\n1266:     node_port: Optional[int] = typer.Option(None, \"--node-port\", help=\"Specific NodePort to use (30000-32767) for K8s deployment\"),\n1267:     replicas: Optional[int] = typer.Option(None, \"--replicas\", help=\"Number of replicas for K8s deployment (default: 1)\"),\n1268:     namespace: Optional[str] = typer.Option(None, \"--namespace\", help=\"The namespace for the deployment\"),\n1269:     verbose: bool = typer.Option(False, \"--verbose\", help=\"Enable detailed logging\"),\n1270: ) -> None:\n1271:     \"\"\"Publish an agent to Kubernetes or AgentCube platform.\"\"\"\n1272:     workspace_path = Path(workspace).resolve()\n1273: \n1274:     with Progress(\n1275:         SpinnerColumn(),\n1276:         TextColumn(\"[progress.description]{task.description}\"),\n1277:         console=console,\n1278:     ) as progress:\n1279:         progress.add_task(description=\"Publishing agent...\", total=None)\n1280: \n1281:         try:\n1282:             runtime = PublishRuntime(verbose=verbose, provider=provider)\n1283:             result = runtime.publish(\n1284:                 workspace_path,\n1285:                 version=version,\n1286:                 image_url=image_url,\n1287:                 image_username=image_username,\n1288:                 image_password=image_password,\n1289:                 description=description,\n1290:                 region=region,\n1291:                 cloud_provider=cloud_provider,\n1292:                 provider=provider,\n1293:                 node_port=node_port,\n1294:                 replicas=replicas,\n1295:                 namespace=namespace,\n1296:             )\n1297: \n1298:             console.print(f\"[green]✓[/green] Successfully published agent: [bold]{result['agent_name']}[/bold]\")\n1299:             console.print(f\"  Provider: {result.get('deployment_type', 'unknown')}\")\n1300:             console.print(f\"  Namespace: {result.get('namespace', 'default')}\")\n1301:             console.print(f\"  Image: {result.get('image_url', 'unknown')}\")\n1302: \n1303:             if result.get('deployment_type') == 'AgentRuntime':\n1304:                 console.print(f\"  Router URL: {result.get('router_url', 'N/A')}\")\n1305:                 console.print(f\"  Workload Manager: {result.get('workload_manager_url', 'N/A')}\")\n1306:                 if result.get('endpoint'):\n1307:                     console.print(f\"  Endpoint: {result['endpoint']}\")\n1308: \n1309:             elif result.get('deployment_type') == 'Kubernetes':\n1310:                 console.print(f\"  Deployment: {result.get('deployment_name', 'N/A')}\")\n1311:                 console.print(f\"  Service: {result.get('service_name', 'N/A')}\")\n1312:                 console.print(f\"  NodePort: {result.get('node_port', 'N/A')}\")\n1313:                 console.print(f\"  Service URL: {result.get('service_url', 'N/A')}\")\n1314:                 console.print(f\"  Replicas: {result.get('replicas', 1)}\")\n1315: \n1316:             console.print(f\"  Status: {result.get('status', 'unknown')}\")\n1317: \n1318:         except Exception as e:\n1319:             _handle_error(e, \"publish\", verbose)\n1320: ```\n1321: \n1322: ### 6. Unit Tests\n1323: \n1324: ```python\n1325: # tests/test_publish_runtime.py\n1326: \"\"\"Tests for PublishRuntime.\"\"\"\n1327: \n1328: import tempfile\n1329: from pathlib import Path\n1330: from unittest.mock import MagicMock, patch\n1331: \n1332: import pytest\n1333: \n1334: from agentcube.runtime.publish_runtime import PublishRuntime\n1335: from agentcube.services.metadata_service import AgentMetadata\n1336: \n1337: \n1338: @pytest.fixture\n1339: def packaged_workspace():\n1340:     \"\"\"Create a temporary packaged workspace.\"\"\"\n1341:     with tempfile.TemporaryDirectory() as tmpdir:\n1342:         workspace = Path(tmpdir)\n1343:         # Create main.py\n1344:         (workspace / \"main.py\").write_text(\"\"\"\n1345: from flask import Flask\n1346: app = Flask(__name__)\n1347: \n1348: @app.route(\"/health\")\n1349: def health():\n1350:     return {\"status\": \"healthy\"}\n1351: \n1352: if __name__ == \"__main__\":\n1353:     app.run(host=\"0.0.0.0\", port=8080)\n1354: \"\"\")\n1355:         # Create requirements.txt\n1356:         (workspace / \"requirements.txt\").write_text(\"flask>=2.0.0\\n\")\n\n(Output capped at 50 KB. Showing lines 1-1356. Use offset=1357 to continue.)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"# AR-022: CLI Publish Command\n\n## Purpose\n\nThis proposal implements the `publish` command for the AgentCube Python CLI toolkit. The `publish` command deploys agents to Kubernetes or AgentCube platform using either the standard Kubernetes provider (Deployment + NodePort Service) or the AgentCube provider (AgentRuntime CR). This command completes the agent deployment workflow after `pack` and `build` commands.\n\nThe goal is to:\n\n1. **Support dual-provider deployment** - Enable deployment to standard Kubernetes (Deployment/Service) or AgentCube platform (AgentRuntime CR) via `--provider` flag\n2. **Handle image preparation** - Prepare container images via local Docker push or accept pre-built image URLs for cloud build mode\n3. **Manage deployment lifecycle** - Create or patch Kubernetes resources, wait for rollout readiness, and report deployment status\n4. **Persist deployment metadata** - Update agent metadata with deployment information including agent_id, endpoint URLs, and session configuration\n\nThis implementation builds upon the CLI toolkit specification (`cli-toolkit/spec.md`, `cli-toolkit/design.md`) and leverages the Kubernetes provider patterns from `deployment/client-go.md`.\n\n## Scope\n\n**Module:** `cmd/cli`  \n**Language:** Python  \n**Size:** L","truncated":true,"loaded":[]},"title":"workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-qwen3.5-plus_20260410T163217Z/changes/AR-022/proposal.md","time":{"start":1775868360866,"end":1775868360896}}}}
